5.5.2 Handling Invalid Input
----------------------------

To further refine the game's behavior, rather than crashing the program
when the user inputs a non-number, let's make the game ignore a
non-number so the user can continue guessing.  We can do that by
altering the line where ‚Äòguess‚Äô is converted from a ‚ÄòString‚Äô to a ‚Äòu32‚Äô,
as shown in Listing 2-5.

