can optionally specify a ‚Äòloop label‚Äô on a loop that you can then use
with ‚Äòbreak‚Äô or ‚Äòcontinue‚Äô to specify that those keywords apply to the
labeled loop instead of the innermost loop.  Loop labels must begin with
a single quote.  Here's an example with two nested loops:

