counting down each time, and then, after the loop, print a message and
exit.

fn main() {
    let mut number = 3;

    while number != 0 {
        println!("{number}!");

        number -= 1;
    }

    println!("LIFTOFF!!!");
}

This construct eliminates a lot of nesting that would be necessary if
you used ‚Äòloop‚Äô, ‚Äòif‚Äô, ‚Äòelse‚Äô, and ‚Äòbreak‚Äô, and it's clearer.  While a
condition evaluates to ‚Äòtrue‚Äô, the code runs; otherwise, it exits the
