fn main() {
    let a = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50];
    let mut index = 0;

    while index < 5 {
        println!("the value is: {}", a[index]);

        index += 1;
    }
}

Here, the code counts up through the elements in the array.  It starts
at index ‚Äò0‚Äô, and then loops until it reaches the final index in the
array (that is, when ‚Äòindex < 5‚Äô is no longer ‚Äòtrue‚Äô).  Running this
code will print every element in the array:

