to take user input and store it?  For these situations, Rust has a
second string type, ‚ÄòString‚Äô.  This type manages data allocated on the
heap and as such is able to store an amount of text that is unknown to
us at compile time.  You can create a ‚ÄòString‚Äô from a string literal
