8.1.1 Using the Field Init Shorthand
------------------------------------

Because the parameter names and the struct field names are exactly the
same in Listing 5-4, we can use the ‚Äòfield init shorthand‚Äô syntax to
rewrite ‚Äòbuild_user‚Äô so it behaves exactly the same but doesn't have the
repetition of ‚Äòusername‚Äô and ‚Äòemail‚Äô, as shown in Listing 5-5.

fn build_user(email: String, username: String) -> User {
    User {
        active: true,
        username,
        email,
        sign_in_count: 1,
