This code succeeds in figuring out the area of the rectangle by calling
the ‚Äòarea‚Äô function with each dimension, but we can do more to make this
code clear and readable.

The issue with this code is evident in the signature of ‚Äòarea‚Äô:

fn area(width: u32, height: u32) -> u32 {

The ‚Äòarea‚Äô function is supposed to calculate the area of one rectangle,
but the function we wrote has two parameters, and it's not clear
anywhere in our program that the parameters are related.  It would be
more readable and more manageable to group width and height together.
