‚Äòfront_of_house‚Äô.  If module A is contained inside module B, we say that
module A is the ‚Äòchild‚Äô of module B and that module B is the ‚Äòparent‚Äô of
module A. Notice that the entire module tree is rooted under the
implicit module named ‚Äòcrate‚Äô.

The module tree might remind you of the filesystem's directory tree on
your computer; this is a very apt comparison!  Just like directories in
a filesystem, you use modules to organize your code.  And just like
