11.1.2.6 Methods for Iterating Over Strings
...........................................

The best way to operate on pieces of strings is to be explicit about
whether you want characters or bytes.  For individual Unicode scalar
values, use the ‚Äòchars‚Äô method.  Calling ‚Äòchars‚Äô on ‚Äú–ó–¥‚Äù separates out
and returns two values of type ‚Äòchar‚Äô, and you can iterate over the
result to access each element:

