‚Äò'a‚Äô.

As humans, we can look at this code and see that ‚Äòstring1‚Äô is longer
than ‚Äòstring2‚Äô, and therefore, ‚Äòresult‚Äô will contain a reference to
‚Äòstring1‚Äô.  Because ‚Äòstring1‚Äô has not gone out of scope yet, a reference
to ‚Äòstring1‚Äô will still be valid for the ‚Äòprintln!‚Äô statement.  However,
the compiler can't see that the reference is valid in this case.  We've
