The ‚Äòassert!‚Äô macro, provided by the standard library, is useful when
you want to ensure that some condition in a test evaluates to ‚Äòtrue‚Äô.
We give the ‚Äòassert!‚Äô macro an argument that evaluates to a Boolean.  If
the value is ‚Äòtrue‚Äô, nothing happens and the test passes.  If the value
is ‚Äòfalse‚Äô, the ‚Äòassert!‚Äô macro calls ‚Äòpanic!‚Äô to cause the test to
