Note that in some languages and test frameworks, the parameters to
equality assertion functions are called ‚Äòexpected‚Äô and ‚Äòactual‚Äô, and the
order in which we specify the arguments matters.  However, in Rust,
they're called ‚Äòleft‚Äô and ‚Äòright‚Äô, and the order in which we specify the
