Result. that indicates either success or an error.  Returning a ‚ÄòResult‚Äô
Instead of Calling ‚Äòpanic!‚Äô We can instead return a ‚ÄòResult‚Äô value that
will contain a ‚ÄòConfig‚Äô instance in the successful case and will
describe the problem in the error case.  We're also going to change the
