the vertical pipes.  The code in the closure can then use the ‚Äòerr‚Äô
value when it runs.

We've added a new ‚Äòuse‚Äô line to bring ‚Äòprocess‚Äô from the standard
library into scope.  The code in the closure that will be run in the
error case is only two lines: we print the ‚Äòerr‚Äô value and then call
‚Äòprocess::exit‚Äô.  The ‚Äòprocess::exit‚Äô function will stop the program
immediately and return the number that was passed as the exit status
