example, even though the closure body still only needs an immutable
reference, we need to specify that ‚Äòlist‚Äô should be moved into the
closure by putting the ‚Äòmove‚Äô keyword at the beginning of the closure
definition.  The new thread might finish before the rest of the main
thread finishes, or the main thread might finish first.  If the main
thread maintained ownership of ‚Äòlist‚Äô but ended before the new thread
did and dropped ‚Äòlist‚Äô, the immutable reference in the thread would be
invalid.  Therefore, the compiler requires that ‚Äòlist‚Äô be moved into the
closure given to the new thread so the reference will be valid.  Try
removing the ‚Äòmove‚Äô keyword or using ‚Äòlist‚Äô in the main thread after the
