$ cd add

Next, in the ‚Äòadd‚Äô directory, we create the ‚ÄòCargo.toml‚Äô file that will
configure the entire workspace.  This file won't have a ‚Äò[package]‚Äô
section.  Instead, it will start with a ‚Äò[workspace]‚Äô section that will
allow us to add members to the workspace.  We also make a point to use
the latest and greatest version of Cargo's resolver algorithm in our
workspace by setting the ‚Äòresolver‚Äô to ‚Äò"2"‚Äô.

by specifying the path to the package with our binary crate; in this
case, that path is ‚Äòadder‚Äô:

Filename: Cargo.toml

[workspace]
