in ‚Äòadd/target‚Äô rather than ‚Äòadd/adder/target‚Äô.  Cargo structures the
‚Äòtarget‚Äô directory in a workspace like this because the crates in a
workspace are meant to depend on each other.  If each crate had its own
‚Äòtarget‚Äô directory, each crate would have to recompile each of the other
crates in the workspace to place the artifacts in its own ‚Äòtarget‚Äô
directory.  By sharing one ‚Äòtarget‚Äô directory, the crates can avoid
unnecessary rebuilding.


