    Finished `dev` profile [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.60s
     Running `target/debug/drop-example`
CustomSmartPointers created.
Dropping CustomSmartPointer with data `other stuff`!
Dropping CustomSmartPointer with data `my stuff`!

Rust automatically called ‚Äòdrop‚Äô for us when our instances went out of
scope, calling the code we specified.  Variables are dropped in the
reverse order of their creation, so ‚Äòd‚Äô was dropped before ‚Äòc‚Äô.  This
example's purpose is to give you a visual guide to how the ‚Äòdrop‚Äô method
works; usually you would specify the cleanup code that your type needs
to run rather than a print message.

