In the test, we're testing what happens when the ‚ÄòLimitTracker‚Äô is told
to set ‚Äòvalue‚Äô to something that is more than 75 percent of the ‚Äòmax‚Äô
value.  First, we create a new ‚ÄòMockMessenger‚Äô, which will start with an
empty list of messages.  Then we create a new ‚ÄòLimitTracker‚Äô and give it
a reference to the new ‚ÄòMockMessenger‚Äô and a ‚Äòmax‚Äô value of 100.  We
call the ‚Äòset_value‚Äô method on the ‚ÄòLimitTracker‚Äô with a value of 80,
which is more than 75 percent of 100.  Then we assert that the list of
messages that the ‚ÄòMockMessenger‚Äô is keeping track of should now have
