change the ‚ÄòMessenger‚Äô trait solely for the sake of testing.  Instead,
we need to find a way to make our test code work correctly with our
existing design.

This is a situation in which interior mutability can help!  We'll store
the ‚Äòsent_messages‚Äô within a ‚ÄòRefCell<T>‚Äô, and then the ‚Äòsend‚Äô method
will be able to modify ‚Äòsent_messages‚Äô to store the messages we've seen.
