smart pointer types, such as ‚ÄòMutex<T>‚Äô and ‚ÄòArc<T>‚Äô, that are safe to
use in concurrent contexts.  The type system and the borrow checker
ensure that the code using these solutions won't end up with data races
or invalid references.  Once you get your code to compile, you can rest
assured that it will happily run on multiple threads without the kinds
of hard-to-track-down bugs common in other languages.  Concurrent
programming is no longer a concept to be afraid of: go forth and make
