We add a default implementation for the ‚Äòcontent‚Äô method that returns an
empty string slice.  That means we don't need to implement ‚Äòcontent‚Äô on
the ‚ÄòDraft‚Äô and ‚ÄòPendingReview‚Äô structs.  The ‚ÄòPublished‚Äô struct will
override the ‚Äòcontent‚Äô method and return the value in ‚Äòpost.content‚Äô.

Note that we need lifetime annotations on this method, as we discussed
in Chapter 10.  We're taking a reference to a ‚Äòpost‚Äô as an argument and
returning a reference to part of that ‚Äòpost‚Äô, so the lifetime of the
returned reference is related to the lifetime of the ‚Äòpost‚Äô argument.

And we're done--all of Listing 18-11 now works!  We've implemented the
state pattern with the rules of the blog post workflow.  The logic
related to the rules lives in the state objects rather than being
scattered throughout ‚ÄòPost‚Äô.

