21.1.3.3 Multiple Patterns
..........................

In ‚Äòmatch‚Äô expressions, you can match multiple patterns using the ‚Äò|‚Äô
syntax, which is the pattern ‚Äòor‚Äô operator.  For example, in the
following code we match the value of ‚Äòx‚Äô against the match arms, the
first of which has an ‚Äòor‚Äô option, meaning if the value of ‚Äòx‚Äô matches
either of the values in that arm, that arm's code will run:

    let x = 1;

    match x {
        1 | 2 => println!("one or two"),
        3 => println!("three"),
        _ => println!("anything"),
    }

This code prints ‚Äòone or two‚Äô.


